The paper deals with clustering of uncertain data objects in spatial databases, which is a common problem in the field of database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of Probability Density Functions (PDF) and Uncertain K-Means algorithm also suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes the use of Voronoi Diagrams from Computational Geometry to improve the performance of the clustering algorithm, indicating a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the use of R*-tree indexing over uncertain data objects suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) as a means of reducing computational cost and pruning overheads.
